Yeah. That unreleased dizzy game lets you walk behind trees that way.<br /><br />It's cool in a platformer when the solid color is the sky, but I'm not personally a huge fan of the single solid color floor required for it in a top down game. That's part of what makes Solstice so special. It actually changes the character's pixels that are behind the background in CHR to transparent, so more than one color can be used for those walls.<br /><br />I should stop being so personal in this thread, though. I suppose a lot of things I say I don't want to do can be done, and sometimes can be done pretty easily.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3504">Kasumi</a> — Tue Dec 13, 2011 9:43 pm</p><hr />
